---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Uses" description="Hardware, software, and tools I use day-to-day.">
  <main id="main" class="prose">
    <h1>What Gary Uses</h1>
    <p>Here's a non-exhaustive list of the hardware, software, and tools I use day-to-day.</p>
    <p>
      My primary personal machine is an M1 Max MacBook Pro (32 GB RAM, 1 TB storage). Thinking of
      upgrading "soon" to an M5 machine, but to be honest, the M1 Max is still more than powerful
      enough for my needs.
    </p>
    <p>
      For my work, I use an M3 Pro MacBook Pro and a Dell XPS Tower which dual-boots Windows 11 and
      Ubuntu. I work on cross-platform software (Mac/Windows/Linux), so I like having native
      hardware for each platform rather than entirely relying on virtual machines.
    </p>
    <p>More to come on additional hardware and software...</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: var(--reading-width);
  }
  .prose p {
    margin: var(--sp-4) 0;
  }
</style>
